  "prompt": "When will the next recession be?",
  "response": "Predicting the exact timing of the next recession is challenging due to the complexity of economic factors involved. Recessions can be influenced by a variety of issues including monetary policy, fiscal policy, global economic conditions, geopolitical events, and unexpected shocks to the economy. Economists, analysts, and institutions like the Federal Reserve regularly monitor and model economic conditions to forecast potential downturns, but specific timing remains uncertain.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it\u2019s best to consult economic reports and analyses from reputable sources such as central banks, government agencies, and financial institutions.",
